OL,3,CFire on Little Sark thought to have
OL,4,Cbeen started by discarded glass bottles
OL,6,FThe fire on Little Sark, which needed
OL,7,Fmore than 400 tonnes of water to bring
OL,8,Fit under control, is thought to have
OL,9,Fbeen started by discarded glass
OL,10,Fbottles.
OL,12,FSark's Chief Fire Officer, Kevin
OL,13,FAdams, said littered glass was found
OL,14,Fin a nearby area and was likely to
OL,15,Fhave accumulated 'over years', after
OL,16,Fbenches were installed there to allow
OL,17,Fpeople to admire the clifftop views.
OL,19,FHe believed the cause was due to
OL,20,Fsunlight shining on pieces of glass
OL,21,Flong enough to spark the fire.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/4
