OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1784054883
OL,3,CFire on Little Sark thought to have
OL,4,Cbeen started by discarded glass bottles
OL,6,FKevin Adams told ITV News 'it was 'the
OL,7,Flargest fire he'd ever seen' and the
OL,8,Ffirst time since Sark's Fire Service's
OL,9,Finception in 1958, that a major
OL,10,Fincident had been declared.
OL,12,FHe added: "Water and resources were
OL,13,Fthe biggest challenge, with 400,000
OL,14,Flitres needed from (Big) Sark, after
OL,15,FLittle Sark's supplies were almost
OL,16,Finstantly depleted."
OL,18,FSince the incident he has urged the
OL,19,Fpublic to properly dispose of
OL,20,Fbarbecues and avoid leaving glass
OL,21,Fbottles behind.
